    <note>Ma(2) Shenwen [24604] Shenwen was the youngest son of Yuehena [24518] and his mingzi deviates from the generational indicators used by all of his elder brothers and probably is a transliteration of a Uighur name. I suspect that the other descendants of Yuehena with non-Chinese names were either sons of Shenwen or the youngest sons of the grandsons of Yuehena. Since all sons of Run [24521] share the same generational names, by this time the completely Sinicized branch of the lineage did not retain what appears to be remnants of the ultimogeniture that characterized the culture of many nomadic peoples including of the Mongols. WDY, 2, 995.</note>
